#: ../../../src/reference/security/disaster-recovery.md:79
msgid ""
"We store all virtual machine images on a distributed storage system "
"(Ceph) with n+2 redundancy. Loss of a single server can be masked "
"transparently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/disaster-recovery.md:82
msgid ""
"We can loose multiple storage servers, depending on the capacity of our "
"cluster. We expect to be able to loose at least 2 servers without "
"impacting service or data availability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/disaster-recovery.md:88
msgid ""
"Ceph performs automatic recovery. Reduced I/O performance may be "
"experienced during this period on virtual machines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../src/reference/security/disaster-recovery.md:91
msgid "RTO: 5 minutes"
msgstr ""

